{
  "texts": [
    "Each dimension corresponds to one of 1600 features at a specific layer of GPT-2.",
    "GPT-2 effectively re-represents the language stimulus as a trajectory in this high-dimensional space, capturing rich syntactic and semantic information.",
    "The regression model used in the present encoding analyses estimates a linear mapping from this geometric representation of the stimulus to the electrode.",
    "However, it cannot nonlinearly alter wordby-word geometry, as it only reweights features without reshaping the embeddings' geometry.",
    "Therefore, without common geometric patterns between contextual and brain embeddings in IFG, we could not predict (zero-shot inference) the brain embeddings for unseen left-out words not seen during training."
  ]
}